#import "../../knot-typst-package/lib.typ": *
#show: codly-init

= Test Phase 2: DataFrame Support

This document tests the new DataFrame support in Knot Phase 2.

== Simple DataFrame

Let's create a simple dataframe and display it:

```{r df-test}
#| eval: true
#| echo: true
#| output: true
df <- data.frame(
  Name = c("Alice", "Bob", "Charlie"),
  Age = c(25, 30, 35),
  Score = c(95.5, 87.3, 92.1)
)
typst(df)
```

== Iris Dataset

Now let's display the first few rows of the iris dataset:

```{r iris-test}
#| eval: true
#| echo: true
#| output: true
typst(head(iris))
```

== Mixed Output

This chunk shows regular text output:

```{r text-output}
#| eval: true
#| echo: true
#| output: true
summary(iris$Sepal.Length)
```
